      "solution": "color=input()\n\nboard=[]\n\nx=0\ny=0\nfor i in range(8):\n    line=input()\n    board.append(line)\n\n    if \"Q\" in line:\n        y=i\n        x=line.find(\"Q\")\n\nnb=0\n\n#vertical\n\ni=y+1\npiece=False\n\nwhile i<8 and piece==False:\n    case=board[i][x]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    i+=1\n\ni=y-1\npiece=False\n\nwhile i>-1 and piece==False:\n    case=board[i][x]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    i-=1\n\n#diagonal 1\ni=y+1\nj=x+1\npiece=False\n\nwhile i<8 and j<8 and piece==False:\n    case=board[i][j]\n\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    i+=1\n    j+=1\n\n\ni=y-1\nj=x-1\npiece=False\n\nwhile i>-1 and j>-1 and piece==False:\n    case=board[i][j]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    i-=1\n    j-=1\n\n#horizontal\nj=x+1\npiece=False\n\nwhile j<8 and piece==False:\n    case=board[y][j]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    j+=1\n\nj=x-1\npiece=False\n\nwhile j>-1 and piece==False:\n    case=board[y][j]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    j-=1\n\n\n\n#diagonal 2\ni=y+1\nj=x-1\npiece=False\n\nwhile i<8 and j>-1 and piece==False:\n    case=board[i][j]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    i+=1\n    j-=1\n\n\ni=y-1\nj=x+1\npiece=False\n\nwhile i>-1 and j<8 and piece==False:\n    case=board[i][j]\n    if case==\".\":\n        nb+=1\n    else:\n        piece=True\n        if case!=color[0]:\n            nb+=1\n    i-=1\n    j+=1\n\n\n\nprint(nb)\n",
      "statement": "Chess is played on an 8x8 board composed of 64 squares. In this game it is important to <<control>> a large amount of these squares to gain the upper hand on the opponent. A square is said to be controlled when it is in the range of movement of a chess piece.\n\nThe chess piece that can control the most squares is <<the queen>>. It can move on any square vertically, horizontally and diagonally.\n\n<<Your mission :>> Create a program able to calculate the number of squares controlled by the queen in a specific given position. \n\n<<A square is considered to be controlled when the queen can move to it.>>\n<<- A square containing a piece of the same [[color]] isn't considered controlled.>>\n<<- But a square containing a piece of the opposite [[color]] can be considered controlled.>>\n<<- The square the queen is currently on isn't counted.>>",
